commit message:
Fix AnySoftKeyboard dictionary loading

It should accept both 'raw' and 'binary' types. AnySoftKeyboard split dicts not yet supported.
Swedish 4-row: remove random 'w' as alternate for 'v'.
Vibrate when changing the 'vibrate duration' setting to provide immediate feedback.

More popup refactoring; add 'disable' and auto-repeat choices

Also get rid of the StateListDrawable for the key preview which wasn't working right, it's supposed to show '...' if there are long-press options available.

Add more examples to the popup contents menu entries to make the effect clearer.
Move some preferences to a new 'Key Feedback' subcategory.
